# Work dotfiles layer — .chezmoiignore
#
# This chezmoi instance shares a target directory ($HOME) with the personal
# dotfiles layer. Without an ignore strategy, chezmoi would treat every file
# from the personal layer as "unmanaged" and, in directories using the exact_
# prefix (like .bash.d), would delete them to enforce its own desired state.
#
# To prevent this, we ignore everything by default and then selectively
# un-ignore only the files that this work layer explicitly manages. This is
# safer than listing personal files to ignore (allowlist approach) because
# any new file added to the personal repo would need to be manually added
# here — a maintenance burden and a source of subtle breakage.
#
# NOTE: When un-ignoring files in subdirectories, each parent directory in the
# path must also be un-ignored — same behavior as .gitignore.

*

# --- Files managed by the work layer ---

# Shell config: doist_* files in bash.d local dirs are tracked by this repo.
# doist_local_* files are machine-specific and NOT tracked by either repo.
#
# Each parent directory must be explicitly un-ignored to allow chezmoi to
# traverse into it. Ignoring * blocks all directory traversal, so without
# these lines chezmoi would never see the files inside.
!.bash.d/
!.bash.d/local/
!.bash.d/local/before/
!.bash.d/local/before/doist_*
.bash.d/local/before/doist_local_*
!.bash.d/local/after/
!.bash.d/local/after/doist_*
.bash.d/local/after/doist_local_*

# Same directory un-ignoring applies to all paths below.
!.config/
!.config/git/
!.config/git/config.work
!.config/starship.toml
!.config/starship-ascii-prompt.toml

!.local/
!.local/bin/
!.local/bin/chezmoi-work
!.local/bin/cheznous
!.local/bin/cheznous-rev

!.ssh/
!.ssh/config.d/
!.ssh/config.d/work
